%I A395609 #9 Jun 16 2026 19:54:02
%S A395609 49,136352,51124091,4582212760,167265198665
%N A395609 Number of satisfiable 3-SAT formulas with n variables and 6 clauses in the multiset clause model.
%C A395609 Clauses are multisets of 3 literals chosen from {x_1, ..., x_n, not x_1, ..., not x_n}; repeated literals inside a clause are allowed. A formula is a multiset of 6 such clauses, so repeated clauses are also allowed.
%C A395609 Together with the m=6 column of A396351, this sequence partitions the set of all 6-clause formulas in the same multiset model into satisfiable and unsatisfiable formulas.
%C A395609 The total number of 6-clause formulas is binomial(C(n)+5,6), where C(n)=binomial(2*n+2,3) is the number of clause types.
%D A395609 Stephen A. Cook, The complexity of theorem-proving procedures, Proceedings of the Third Annual ACM Symposium on Theory of Computing, 1971, 151-158.
%F A395609 a(n) = binomial(binomial(2*n+2,3)+5,6) - A396351(n,6).
%Y A395609 Cf. A396351, A396492, A396493, A395546.
%K A395609 nonn,hard,more
%O A395609 1,1
%A A395609 _Ramin Mohammadi Masoudi_, Jun 13 2026
